{"author":{"id":"138b13306404778af60b1d60d606624fec41556ddac480b2d5f762806ce84fed"},"ops":[{"type":1,"timestamp":1782958625,"nonce":"zV1jSFiJl+IgeGLlquqrt0Cn83c=","kind":"spec","title":"kref `ls` shell output, columns, and entry reattribution — design","content_type":"text/markdown"},{"type":3,"timestamp":1782958625,"nonce":"5l7oMLDPj1IVTW/is8lSgvSJ0Iw=","body":"# kref `ls` shell output, columns, and entry reattribution — design\n\n- **Date:** 2026-06-27\n- **Status:** Approved (pending implementation)\n- **Scope:** three CLI papercuts on `kref list`/`kref update`, surfaced while\n  dogfooding the docs-into-kb migration.\n\n## Motivation\n\nThree gaps felt during real use:\n\n1. No machine-greppable listing. Extracting ids for a pipeline required\n   `kref list --json | python3 -c ...`. A shell-friendly format that honors the\n   existing filters and pipes through `grep`/`cut`/`xargs` is missing.\n2. `kref ls` shows a fixed five-column table. There is no way to see who authored\n   an entry or when it changed without `kref show` per entry.\n3. No way to (re)attribute an entry's author. `CreatedBy` is fixed at creation;\n   an entry ingested under the wrong identity stays mis-attributed forever.\n\n## Decisions\n\n### D1 — `kref ls` output modes\n\nThree mutually exclusive modes:\n\n- **default** — the existing pretty, tier-sorted, collapsed table. Unchanged.\n- **`--json`** — existing full-object JSON. Unchanged.\n- **`--plain`** — new shell mode. Tab-separated selected columns, one entry per\n  line, **no header, no footer, no color, no tier glyph**. Lists every matching\n  entry **uncollapsed** (no `×N` title grouping), because scripts want the\n  complete filtered set, not representatives. Superseded/deleted are still\n  excluded unless `--all` is given (consistent with the table's row selection\n  aside from collapsing).\n\n`--plain` combined with `--json` is an error.\n\n### D2 — column selection\n\nApplies to the **default table** and **`--plain`** modes (not `--json`):\n\n- **`--columns a,b,c`** — choose and order columns by friendly name.\n- **`--wide`** — preset shorthand equal to\n  `tier,id,kind,status,author,updated,title`.\n- Default (neither flag) — `tier,id,kind,status,title` (today's table).\n- `--columns` and `--wide` together is an error (ambiguous).\n- `--columns`/`--wide` combined with `--json` is an error (JSON is already the\n  full object).\n\nColumn tokens (unknown token → error listing valid tokens):\n\n| token     | renders                                             |\n|-----------|-----------------------------------------------------|\n| `tier`    | table: `glyph word` badge; plain: bare word         |\n| `id`      | 12-char short id (prefix-resolvable)                |\n| `fullid`  | 64-char full id                                     |\n| `kind`    | kind                                                |\n| `status`  | status                                              |\n| `title`   | title (table keeps the `[labels] ◆ merged (×N) (deleted)` suffixes; plain emits the bare title) |\n| `author`  | `CreatedBy` display name                            |\n| `email`   | `CreatedByEmail`                                    |\n| `created` | `CreatedAt` as `YYYY-MM-DD`                          |\n| `updated` | `UpdatedAt` as `YYYY-MM-DD`                          |\n| `labels`  | comma-joined labels                                 |\n| `tracked` | `yes`/`no`                                           |\n| `path`    | `TrackedPath` (empty when untracked)                |\n\nPrecise timestamps remain the job of `--json`. There is no `--ids` shorthand:\nthe id-only case is `kref ls --plain --columns id`.\n\nThe `×N` collapse count is a table-only affordance and is not a column token; in\nplain mode every entry is its own line, so the count is unnecessary.\n\n### D3 — reattribution (`kref update`)\n\n`CreatedBy`/`CreatedByEmail` are set only by the immutable `Create` op, so\nreattribution is a **new append-only operation `Reattribute{name,email}`** whose\n`Apply` overwrites `s.CreatedBy`/`s.CreatedByEmail`. The op is itself authored by\nthe current identity, so `kref log` gains an honest \"reattributed by \u003cyou\u003e\"\nentry — no history is rewritten, consistent with the DAG model and the unsigned\nattribution already documented in the spec.\n\nTwo `kref update` flags:\n\n- **`--reset-author`** (bool) — reattribute to the current kref identity\n  (`Store.Author()`), git's `--reset-author` semantic.\n- **`--author \"Name \u003cemail\u003e\"`** (string) — reattribute to an explicit author.\n  Parsed strictly; malformed input (no `\u003cemail\u003e` form, empty name, empty email)\n  is an error.\n- The two flags are mutually exclusive (error if both set).\n- Both work **standalone**: the `update` \"nothing to update\" guard is relaxed so\n  `kref update \u003cid\u003e --reset-author` with no body/title/kind is valid. When only\n  reattribution is requested, no body/title/kind ops are appended.\n\n## Components touched\n\n- `internal/entry/operations.go` — new `Reattribute` op (`OperationType` const,\n  struct, `NewReattribute`, `Id`/`Validate`/`Apply`, registration in\n  `operationUnmarshaler`).\n- `internal/store/store.go` — `Reattribute(id, name, email)` appends the op via\n  the store author.\n- `internal/render/render.go` — column model: a `Column` token set, a\n  `RenderList(w, items, opts)` path that drives both the aligned table and the\n  TSV plain output from one ordered column list. The existing `List` behavior is\n  the default-columns table path.\n- `cmd/kref/commands.go` — `list`: `--plain`, `--columns`, `--wide` flags, parse\n  + validate (mutual exclusions), pass column spec to render; `update`:\n  `--reset-author`, `--author`, guard relaxation, mutual exclusion, author\n  string parsing.\n\n## Testing (TDD)\n\n- **entry**: `Reattribute.Apply` overwrites author; `Validate` rejects empty\n  name/email; round-trips through `operationUnmarshaler`.\n- **store**: `Reattribute` changes `Get(id)` author; appears in `Log`.\n- **render**: each column token renders expected cell (table + plain); `--plain`\n  is TSV with no header/footer/color; unknown token errors; `--wide` preset;\n  uncollapsed in plain vs collapsed in table.\n- **cmd/kref**: `--plain --columns id` emits bare ids honoring filters;\n  `--columns`+`--json` errors; `--columns`+`--wide` errors; `--reset-author`\n  standalone; `--author \"N \u003ce\u003e\"`; both-flags error; malformed `--author` error.\n\n## Out of scope (YAGNI)\n\n`-o` ps-style format string, per-column header renaming, custom date/time\nformats, configurable collapsing in plain mode. Revisit only on demand."}]}